text.section: A support order or income-withholding order issued in another state or a foreign support order is registered when the order is filed in the registering tribunal of this state.
A registered support order issued in another state or foreign country is enforceable in the same manner and is subject to the same procedures as an order issued by a tribunal of this state.

Except as otherwise provided in Article 6 of this chapter, a tribunal of this state shall recognize and enforce, but may not modify, a registered support order if the issuing tribunal had jurisdiction.

law.history: Amended 2015 Ky. Acts ch. 18, sec. 42, effective June 24, 2015. -- Contingent effective date repealed 1998 Ky. Acts ch. 101, sec. 20, effective March 23, 1998. -- Created 1996 Ky. Acts ch. 365, sec. 48, effective upon contingency.
